    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Home Depot board's decision to oust Robert L. Nardelli as chairman and chief executive is a surprising move that highlights the growing influence of investors. But it also illustrates another point: Even when their voice is heard on executive pay, shareholders often wind up holding the bag. Page C4.</p>
